node.title: Live: NZ enters red as Omicron circulates in Auckland, possibly Nelson
node.description: Here's what you need to know.
node.content: ["New Zealanders are waking up to the red setting of the 'traffic light' system after a number of people tested positive for the highly infectious Omicron variant over the weekend.", "On Sunday, it was revealed that nine people in the Nelson-Marlborough region were carrying the variant. The cases had also travelled to Auckland to attend a wedding.", "An Air New Zealand flight attendant has also tested positive for the variant and had worked on domestic flights while infectious.", "Speaking at a press conference on Sunday morning, Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern confirmed the variant is circulating in Auckland and\u00a0likely elsewhere in New Zealand, announcing that the nation will shift into red, the most restrictive setting of the COVID-19 Protection Framework,\u00a0from 11:59pm.", "Follow Newshub's live updates below - app users, click here", "7:25am - Kia ora, good morning, and welcome to Newshub's live coverage on the COVID-19 outbreak for Monday, January 24."]
